污染預防與永續物料管理                  


  	課程大綱及進度表 Course Outline and Schedule
開課系所
Department/Institute	Environmental Engineering Institute
環工所

開課學期 Semester	2 學期
課程名稱(中文)
Course Title (Chinese)	污染預防與永續物料管理
課程名稱（英文）
Course Title (English)	Pollution Prevention and Sustainable Materials Management
課程碼 Course Code	P556700
分班碼 Class Code	N/A
先修科目或先備能力
Prerequisite	Bachelor’s Degree in Science, Engineering or equivalent

學分數 Credit	3
開課教師 Teacher	Prof. Chih C. Chao巢志成教授
e-mail	ccchao@mail.ncku.edu.tw
電話 Telephone	0932-379-194
Office Hours	Monday morning
課程概述（中文、英文）
Course Description	In the past 50 years, humans have consumed more resources than in all previous history. Significant changes in the course are required to achieve sustainability.
Conventionally, various engineering disciplines taught in universities were fairly segregated; each focuses on a narrowly defined design and manufacturing function without consideration of its environmental consequences. This is no longer acceptable in the industry, where pollution prevention and waste minimization have become very important. This rapidly changing industrial emphasis was initially in response to regulatory pressure, but now it is driven primarily by economics. Industries are striving to minimize waste generation at source, to reuse more of the waste materials that are generated, and to design products for easier disassembly and reuse after their useful lifetime is completed. Modern industries have started to realize that by minimizing end-of-pipe type of treatment, often, economic competitiveness is also acquired. 
In line with the current and future trend, this course is designed to acquaint the students with the concepts and principles of pollution prevention and sustainable materials management, and build up their basic skills in these areas by reviewing and practicing case studies. 

教學目標
Course Objectives	The objective of this course is to introduce the principles of pollution prevention, sustainable materials management, environmentally benign products, processes and manufacturing systems. Students will learn the impacts of wastes from manufacturing and post-use product disposal, environmental cycles of materials, sustainability, and principles of environmental economics. Materials selection, process, and product design, and packaging are addressed. Case studies will also be conducted to train the students in problem-solving skills. 

授課課程大綱明細
Course Outlines	1.	Pollution Prevention Principles
2.	Pollution Prevention Applications
3.	Pollution Prevention Case Studies
4.	Sustainable Materials Management Overview
5.	Dematerialization Principles and Applications
6.	Detoxification Principles and Applications
7.	Internalization of Externalities
8.	Selection of Compatible Materials
9.	Industrial Ecology Overview
10.	Eco-Industrial Development Principles and Applications

參考書目
References	1.  Lecture Notes of Prof. Chih C. Chao
2.  Pollution Prevention Fundamentals
 and Practice, P. L. Bishop
3. Pollution Prevention: Homework & Design Problems for Engineering Curriculum, D. T. Allen et al.
4.  Pollution Prevention through Process Integration, Mahmound M. El-Halwagi
5.  Perspectives of Industrial Ecology, D. Bourg & S. Erkman

課程要求
Course Requirements	No specific requirements 

